2016 Gusto Benefits

Health Benefits Renewal

Gusto makes it refreshingly easy to take care of payroll, HR, and benefits for small business owners. This project allows companies who currently offer health benefits for their employees, to renew benefits for the upcoming year.

There were two main design phases, pre-launch design iterations and post-launch improvements iterations. As the design owner, I was responsible for defining the project with the product managers, creating and testing the designs, and implementing the UI components for the project.

Role
  • Design
  • Research
  • Front-end
Team
  • 1 Product Manager
  • 3 Engineers

01 Define Feature Requirements and Information Architecture

I worked closely with the product manager on defining the users and use cases. I created a user journey map to visualize the key steps and data points, and helped us better understand the problem and contraints.

  • e.g.
  • Persona: a novice small business owner (a.k.a. employer)
  • Scenario: renewing health plans for the first time
  • User needs: pick new health plans that have better coverages while keeping the cost the same
  • Goal: allow users to give us feedback about their current health plans, and provide plan recommendations that meet their needs
